        <div class="tab-pane" id="Contexts">
            <div class="api-info span10 row">
                Contexts are effectively containers for Achievement Classes.  You'll want to create a context
                for each property you want to associate achievements with.  For instance, you might want to
                create a Context for a video game, or a website, or your business.  You can associate information
                like a url and an image with a context that will help users to identify it.
            </div>
            
            <div class="span10 row">
                <div class="api-url span10 bottomed">
                    <h3>/api/1.0/Context (POST)</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="api-explanation span10">
                    <h4>Creates a new context.</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="api-arguments span7">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Parameter</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>name</b></td>
                                <td>string</td>
                                <td>The context name.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>description</b></td>
                                <td>string</td>
                                <td>A description for the context.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>image</b></td>
                                <td>string (url)</td>
                                <td>A url for a context image. (Note: If you manage contexts through the web interface, we allow you to upload an image that we will host for you that this field will be set to.)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>url</b></td>
                                <td>string (url)</td>
                                <td>A url for the context.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    
                    <h6>Example Request Body:</h6>
                    <pre class="prettyprint">
{
    name: "Test Context",
    description: "This is a test context.",
    image: "http://testcontext.com/logo.png",
    url: "http://testcontext.com/"
}
                    </pre>
                </div>
                <div class="api-notes extra span2">
                    <b>Requires authentication/an existing session as a user.</b>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="span10 row">
                <div class="api-url span10 bottomed">
                    <h3>/api/1.0/Context/:contextId (PUT)</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="api-explanation span10">
                    <h4>Updates an existing context specified by :contextId.</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="api-arguments span7">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Parameter</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>name</b></td>
                                <td>string</td>
                                <td>The context name.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>description</b></td>
                                <td>string</td>
                                <td>A description for the context.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>image</b></td>
                                <td>string (url)</td>
                                <td>A url for a context image.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>url</b></td>
                                <td>string (url)</td>
                                <td>A url for the context.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><b>owners</b></td>
                                <td>array</td>
                                <td>An array of email md5 hashes that have ownership permissions for the context.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    
                    <h6>Example Request Body:</h6>
                    <pre class="prettyprint">
{
    name: "New Context",
    description: "This is a new context!",
    image: "http://newcontext.com/logo.png",
    url: "http://newcontext.com/",
    owners: [ "2d037f6a385d2874813417119d1be6f9", "0a52192c48cf7c71dadc2202d068a8f9" ]
}
                    </pre>
                </div>
                <div class="api-notes extra span2">
                    <b>Requires authentication/an existing session as an owner of the given context.</b>
                    <p>
                    <h3>WARNING!</h3>
                    The 'owners' field replaces the existing value, it does not append/remove from it.
                    Therefore, you should be careful when sending this field that you set it to all
                    owners you want to be able to control the context.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
